1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bb5 Bb4 5. O-O O-O 6. d3 d6 7. Bg5 Ne7!? { a nice move to throw off the symmetry and create some dynamic imbalances } 8. Bxf6 gxf6 9. Nh4 c6 10. Ba4 Ng6 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. Bb3 { black to move -- how to
continue? } 12... Kg7! 13. f4 Rh8 14. fxe5 dxe5 15. Qf3 a5 16. a4 Bc5+ 17. Kh1 Rxh2+ (17... Rh4 { objectively the best continuation, black is better off building up
pressure rather than going completely insane }) 18. Kxh2 Qh8+ 19. Kg3 f5 20. d4 f4+ 21. Kf2 Qh4+ 22. Ke2 (22. g3! { the engine move -- if white defends
correctly, he should have a decisive advantage }) 22... Bxd4 23. g3 Qh2+ 24. Kd3 (24. Ke1 { safer }) 24... Be3 25. Ne2 Bh3 26. Rh1 Rd8+ 27. Kc3 { black to move,
mate in 4! } 27... Bd2+ 28. Kc4 b6 29. g4 Qxe2+ { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


